      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEXT TUESDAY (7) looks nicely placed. Two runs to date have been good, working home well in a stronger maiden last time in town for a distant second to a smart one. Up an extra 100m in trip will suit this daughter of Dundeel and she looks set to break through. HARDUNBY (3) is another progeny of Dundeel, a gelding for the Hayes yard who debuts over a good trip. He's been jumping out well enough to figure at big odds. THE CABLE GUY (5) tried hard up on speed on debut here over 1500m behind one with handy maiden form. He can only improve off that and looks a strong chance. THE QUIET IMMORTAL (6) has been good in three runs back and looks nicely suited to a mile now.",
